---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import WorkCard from '../components/WorkCard.astro';
import StripeDivider from '../components/StripeDivider.astro';
import { work } from '../data/work';
---

<Layout
  title="Contract WordPress Developer | WP Indy"
  description="Senior contract WordPress and PHP developer for custom builds, API integrations, WooCommerce work, inherited sites, and agency support."
>
  <section class="shell py-20">
    <p class="eyebrow">Contract WordPress Developer</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl text-white">Senior contract WordPress/PHP developer<br/>for custom builds, integrations, and inherited sites.</h1>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-white/80">I’m Tommy Day, an Indianapolis-based WordPress/PHP developer with 15+ years of production experience building custom plugins, API integrations, ecommerce workflows, CMS architecture, and backend tooling.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-white/80">I work with agencies, internal teams, and direct clients who need someone senior enough to jump into an existing codebase, understand the business problem, and ship maintainable solutions without a lot of hand-holding.</p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
        <a href="mailto:tommy@wpindy.com?subject=Contract%20WordPress%20Developer%20Inquiry" class="btn-pill btn-pill--blue">Contact Tommy</a>
        <a href="/services/" class="underline">View Services</a>
        <a href="/work/" class="underline">View Work</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <StripeDivider />

  <section class="bg-[#f6f3ee] text-neutral-900">
    <div class="shell py-16">
      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Best fit for</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 max-w-3xl">I’m most useful on WordPress projects where the work goes beyond basic theme edits or plugin configuration.</p>

      <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4">
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Custom WordPress plugin development</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">WordPress/PHP contract roles</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">API integrations & third-party data sync</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">WooCommerce customization & ecommerce logic</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">ACF-heavy content architecture</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Gutenberg / block editor builds</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Custom admin dashboards & reporting tools</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">Inherited sites: debugging, cleanup, refactoring</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-3xl border border-black/10 bg-white/55 p-6">
          <div class="text-base font-semibold">White-label agency development</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="bg-white py-16 text-neutral-900">
    <div class="shell">
  <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Relevant project experience</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 max-w-3xl">A few examples of the kind of WordPress/PHP work I’m usually brought in to handle.</p>

  <div class="mt-8 grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <!-- select relevant work items from the shared data source -->
        {(() => {
          const slugs = [
            'st-julian-commerce7-wordpress-build',
            'ai-search-plugin-admin-reporting',
            'custom-woocommerce-checkout-flow',
            'woocommerce-loop-course-extension',
          ];

          const items = work.filter((w) => slugs.includes(w.slug)).slice(0, 4);
          return items.map((item) => (
            <WorkCard item={item} />
          ));
        })()}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <StripeDivider />

  <section class="bg-[#e7dfd2] text-neutral-900">
    <div class="shell py-16">
  <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">How I work</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 max-w-3xl">I’m comfortable working independently or embedded with an existing team. I’ve worked as a solo developer, agency developer, subcontractor, white-label partner, and long-term technical resource for clients who need continuity across complex WordPress projects.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-neutral-700 max-w-3xl">I’m especially useful when the work is a little messy: inherited codebases, unclear business logic, aging plugins, custom data structures, third-party APIs, ecommerce edge cases, and projects where someone needs to calmly figure out what’s actually going on.</p>

      <ul class="mt-6 list-inside list-disc max-w-3xl text-neutral-800">
        <li>Clear communication</li>
        <li>Comfortable with existing codebases</li>
        <li>Good fit for agency overflow</li>
        <li>Senior-level debugging and implementation</li>
        <li>Practical, maintainable solutions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <StripeDivider />

  <section class="bg-white py-16 text-neutral-900">
    <div class="shell">
  <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Experience snapshot</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-neutral-800">
        <li>15+ years of freelance and contract WordPress/PHP development</li>
        <li>Former Senior Software Developer at Maestro Learning</li>
        <li>Former agency Web Developer at MilesHerndon</li>
        <li>Co-founder and lead developer of Whirl Sites</li>
        <li>Ongoing white-label and subcontract development for agency partners</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-[#f6f3ee] text-neutral-900">
    <div class="shell py-16">
  <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Core stack</h2>
      <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
        {['WordPress','PHP','JavaScript','WooCommerce','ACF','Gutenberg','REST APIs','Custom plugins','Composer','Git','CLI','Astro','CSS/SCSS'].map((t) => (
          <span class="rounded-full bg-white/60 px-3 py-1 text-sm text-neutral-800 border border-black/10">{t}</span>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-16 text-neutral-900">
    <div class="shell">
  <h2 class="font-display text-2xl">Looking at my resume for a contract role?</h2>
      <p class="mt-3 text-neutral-700 max-w-3xl">This page is the short version. My resume has the full employment history, but the main thing to know is that I’m strongest when a WordPress project needs custom backend thinking, integration work, debugging, or senior-level technical ownership.</p>

      <div class="mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-4">
        <a href="mailto:tommy@wpindy.com?subject=Contract%20WordPress%20Developer%20Inquiry" class="btn-pill btn-pill--blue">Email Tommy</a>
        <!-- TODO: Add sanitized public resume PDF at /public/files/tommy-day-wordpress-developer-resume.pdf -->
        <a href="/contact/" class="underline">Contact page</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
